@node "STARTUPPLUS" "How to use StartupPlus"
                      @{b}How to use StartupPlus@{ub}


 @{b}First Time Users:@{ub}
 After installing StartupPlus you will find that there are a few more files
 lying around on your Hard Drive.  Now in the "WBStartup" drawer.  You will
 find this drawer on your SYS:  drive.  There should be a program called
 StartupPlus.  No click once on the Icon and use the WBench menu to edit
 the Icon's information or press LAmiga+i. They both do the same job.

 To load the data file you will need to place the DATAFILE ToolType into
 the icon. There should all ready be a template for it. If there is just
 click on it and edit away.

 e.g. DATAFILE=ENV:DataFile.sup2
 NB. SUP 1.5 uses the ext. '.sup2' if you try to pass any other extion you
 will get an error message.

 There are also some more @{b}Tool Types@{ub} in the Icon which can be set
 if you wish.  There not essicential and there is all ready a default set
 for the program.  see @{" Tool Types " link "TOOLTYPES" 0}

 @{b}Calling up the Ask Window@{ub}
 There are three ways of doing this procedure.

 First their is the mouse. Just click on the main window with any of the
 mouse buttons. This will open the Ask Window.

 Secondly their is the Keyboard. By pressing the Left or Right Shift Keys
 at startup time this will open the Ask Window.


 @{b}Disabling the program at Startup@{ub}

 @{b}LowLevel Method:@{ub}
 If you want to kill SUP before it loads hold down either of the SHIFT keys.
 This will efficently disable it. If you are all ready in SUP hold down the
 ESC key. This will Terminate the program saftly.

 @{b}HighLevel Method:@{ub}
 If you have the Main window open and active (Making it active can only be
 acheved by clicking on the window. This will, open the Ask Window) you will
 be able to use The Left and Right Shift keys here as well.  The reason for
 not having the main window active is so that if you have a CLI/SHELL screen
 open it will not become deactiveated.


 @{b}Using the Ask Window@{ub}
 New for version 1.4. There is now a menu bar.

 Project:
     Abort    LAmiga+a <--- Aborts the whole program
     -----------------
     About           ? <--- About StartupPlus and registration Details
     About MUI...      <--- About MUI and the version you are using
     -----------------
     Continue LAmiga+c <--- Continue with execution sequence

 Settings:
     Settings MUI...   <--- Call the MUI Prefs program


 There are two listviewers. The one on the left contains all programs with
 the Skip or Ask flags set. The other is contains nothing. Now by dragging
 one of the programs from the left listviewer over to the right listviever,
 the program will be added to the execution sequence.  When you press the
 @{b}'Continue with Execution Sequence'@{ub} button, anything that is now in that
 right listviewer will be executed.

 NB.  If you drag something over to the right listviewer that you know has
      the Ask Flag set, then drag it back again, that ask flag will be
      removed and replaced with a skip flag.  Any Drag 'n' Drop you make
      via the Ask window will not be saved.  So don't worry if you don't
      know what you are doing.  It will all come clear.

 @{b}Changing the datafile at startup@{ub}
 By holding down the Left or Right Alt keys during startup, this calls up
 an ASL FileRequester. Just choose a diffrent file for loading and press
 the OK gadget. Normaly situated in the bottom left of the window.

 To set the Directory of where you keep your datafiles, edit the Icon with
 a line like this one:

 e.g. DATADIR=ENVARC:

 This will set the directory to use. If there is no directory set in the
 Icon, SUP will use the startup directory. In most cases this will be
 'SYS:WBStartup'.


 @{b}Changing the Background@{ub}
 Not an easy task but it is possible.
 · First open the @{b}MUI preferences@{ub} program. If you don't have it,
   why not!
 · You can either do this via the MUI program or via StartupPlus's 'Ask'
   Window under 'Settings/Settings MUI...'. You might also have a
   dropdown menu in the right hand corner of the window.
 · Now goto the menu and under @{i}Project@{ui} you will find an @{i}Open@{ui} Function.
   Use it.
 · Now you should have file requester. Press on the @{b}'Volumes'@{ub} button
   and then find and click on @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}. When the listviewer has finished
   displaying the @{i}'EnvArc:'@{ui} directory click on @{b}'MUI'@{ub} directory.
 · Click on @{b}'STARTUPPLUS.prefs'@{ub} and then on the @{b}'OK'@{ub} button.
 · If you haven't yet got a file called @{b}STARTUPPLUS.prefs@{ub} don't
   worry. Either run @{b}StartupPlus@{ub} or when you come to same the file
   then give it the name @{b}STARTUPPLUS.prefs@{ub}.
 · The preferences file should now be loaded in to MUI.
 · You might have noticed that there is no change in the way the MUI
   Prefrences looks.  Ok, so click on the test button to initial the
   changed preferences.  If there is still no physical diffrence don't
   worry.  You just can't see it yet.
 · Now click on the bit marked @{b}Windows@{ub} in the MUI Listviewer.
 · The window should change it apperance, with new gadgets and options.
 · In the top right hand corner of this window is an borded section named
   @{b}Background@{ub}.
 · Now you should be aware of two boxes, one named @{b}'Window'@{ub} and the other
   called @{b}'Requester'@{ub}.
 · Click on the box with @{b}'Window'@{ub} printed below it and a new smaller window
   will apper called @{b}'Abjust Background'@{ub}.
 · There are three pages to choose from. @{b}'Pattern' 'Color'@{ub} and @{b}'Bitmap'@{ub}

 @{b}@{i}Pattern:@{ub}@{ui}
        · Under 'Pattern' you have to choice of 18 diffrent patterns.
        · Choose a colour or pattern and click on @{b}'OK'@{ub}.
        1 Now the @{i}'Window'@{ui} should have changed to the pattern or colour
          you have just chosen.
        2 Now go back to the menu and choose @{b}'Save As'@{ub}.
        3 Now you should have file requester. Press on the @{b}'Volumes'@{ub}
          button and then click on @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}. When the listviewer has
          finished displaying the @{i}'EnvArc:'@{ui} dir click on @{b}'MUI'@{ub}
          directory.
        4 Click on @{b}'STARTUPPLUS.prefs'@{ub} and then on the @{b}'OK'@{ub}
          button.
        5 Do steps 2 to 4 again but this time you want @{b}'Env:'@{ub} and not
          @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}.
        6 When you have saved both of these files click on the @{b}'Cancel'@{ub}
          button. @{i}Do not click on the the @{b}Save@{ub} button. This will
          save you new preferences as a global preference for all MUI
          applications.@{ui}

 @{b}@{i}Color:@{ub}@{ui}
        · Under @{b}'Color'@{ub} there are three More pages.
          @{b}'MUI' 'Colormap'@{ub} and  @{b}'RGB'@{ub}
        1 Choose a page and colour and click on @{b}'OK'@{ub}.
        2 Now the @{i}'Window'@{ui} should have changed to the colour you have
          just chosen.
        3 Now go back to the menu and choose @{b}'Save As'@{ub}.
        4 Now you should have file requester. Press on the @{b}'Volumes'@{ub}
          button and then click on @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}. When the listviewer has
          finished displaying the @{i}'EnvArc:'@{ui} dir click on @{b}'MUI'@{ub}
          directory.
        5 Click on @{b}'STARTUPPLUS.1.prefs'@{ub} and then on the @{b}'OK'@{ub}
          button.
        6 Do steps 3 to 5 again but this time you want @{b}'Env:'@{ub} and not
          @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}.
        7 When you have saved both of these files click on the @{b}'Cancel'@{ub}
          button. @{i}Do not click on the the @{b}Save@{ub} button. This will
          save you new preferences as a global preference for all MUI
          applications.@{ui}

 @{b}@{i}Bitmap:@{ub}@{ui}
        · Either enter the path and name of the picture you want to display.
        · You can use the get button at the end of the string gadget to
          get the path and name of a picture.
        1 Now the @{i}'Window'@{ui} should have changed to the picture you have
          just chosen.
        2 Now go back to the menu and choose @{b}'Save As'@{ub}.
        3 Now you should have file requester. Press on the @{b}'Volumes'@{ub}
          button and then click on @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}. When the listviewer has
          finished displaying the @{i}'EnvArc:'@{ui} dir click on @{b}'MUI'@{ub}
          directory.
        4 Click on @{b}'STARTUPPLUS.prefs'@{ub} and then on the @{b}'OK'@{ub}
          button.
        5 Do steps 2 to 4 again but this time you want @{b}'Env:'@{ub} and not
          @{b}'EnvArc:'@{ub}.
        6 When you have saved both of these files click on the @{b}'Cancel'@{ub}
          button. @{i}Do not click on the the @{b}Save@{ub} button. This will
          save you new preferences as a global preference for all MUI
          applications.@{ui}


@node "TOOLTYPES" "Whats in the Icon..."

                            @{b}What bit does what@{ub}

 @{b}TOOLTYPES@{ub}
 STARTPRI/n     - The Priority which the StartupPlus has at startup time.
                  Must have a value between +128 to -127. Default is 0

 DONOTWAIT      - Tells WorkBench not to wait for the program to return.
                  DO NOT REMOVE!

 DISABLED/b     - Boolean value (TRUE OR FALSE). By setting the value to
                  TRUE,  StartupPlus will not execute the sequence.
                  Default value is FALSE.

 DATAFILE/s     - The name and location of the datafile to be executed.
                  No default. Just create the datafile and add the name and
                  location in here.

 DATADIR/s      - Holds the directory path of you datafiles.

 HOTKEYS/f      - Calls up the Ask Window via a Hot Keys Flag values are
                  (LSHIFT|RSHIFT) No defaults. Don't press the 'ESC' key.
                  That will send a QUIT flag and stop the program no matter
                  what it is doing. Its safe to use.

 ASKATSTARTUP/b - Boolean value (TRUE OR FALSE). Brings up the Ask Window
                  at startup. Default is FALSE.

 VOIDASK/b      - Boolean value (TRUE OR FALSE). Plane and simply it takes
                  all values that are ASK and looks as them as though they
                  are SKIP. This way you don't get the requester asking you
                  to choose YES or NO. Default is TRUE.

@endnode


